4. (22, -23) = outside layer 22, so in layer 23
5. (23, -23) = on layer 23
6. (24, -23) = on layer 24
7. (24, -22) = on layer 24  
8. (24, -21) = on layer 24

Layer 22 bottom edge: Goes from (22, -22) to (-22, -22)
The right corner (22, -22) has 2025. Moving left along bottom: 2024, 2023, ...
So (22, -21) = 2024

Layer 23: After going up the right edge, it goes along the top, then down the left, then along the bottom.
- Right edge: positions (23, y) for y from -22 to 22 (45 numbers)
- Top edge: positions (x, 23) for x from 22 to -23 (46 numbers)  
- Left edge: positions (-23, y) for y from 22 to -23 (46 numbers)
- Bottom edge: positions (x, -23) for x from -22 to 22 (45 numbers)

Position (22, -23) is on the bottom edge of layer 23.
Going around: 2026 + 45 + 46 + 46 gets us to (-22, -23), then we go right.
So (22, -23) = 2026 + 45 + 46 + 46 + 44 = 2026 + 181 = 2207

Position (23, -23) = 2207 + 1 = 2208

For layer 24 (starts at 2210):
